<span class="displaytext"><i> excerpt from "mitt got the candidate, fred gets the worker" </i> <p><i> jonathan martin </i> </p><p><i> the politico </i> </p><p><i> december 21, 2007 </i> </p><p>tom tancredo may have gotten behind (candidate full) yesterday, but the tanc's top guy on the ground in iowa will help out fred. </p><p>a retired marine and active farmer, bill salier had served as tancredo's iowa state chair. he's a true believing social conservative who ran an uphill race in the '02 gop senate primary that raised some eyebrows. </p><p>in short: he's the sort of worker bee a campaign likes to have on its side. if salier puts his shoulder to the wheel for fred, he could be a major asset. </p><p>... </p><p><i> to view the video of bill salier endorsing (candidate full), please visit: </i> </p><p><a href="http://fredfile.fred08.com/blog/2007/bill-salier-endorses-fred/"> http://fredfile.fred08.com/blog/2007/bill-salier-endorses-fred/ </a> </p><p><i> to view the entire article please visit </i> <i> : </i> </p><p><a href="http://www.politico.com/blogs/jonathanmartin/1207/mitt_got_the_candidate_fred_gets_the_worker.html"> http://www.politico.com/blogs/jonathanmartin/1207/mitt_got_the_candidate_fred_gets_the_worker.html </a></p></span>



